Excellent. Hard to say whether the pureed version or the chunky one is better. The puree is very tasty and has some chewiness if your use an immersion blender. It would be great for someone on a low sodium diet. Once the vegetables are blended, there is so much flavor that salt is irrelevant. But the chunky version (just a cup or two of the soup pureed) preserves the great mouthfeel of the French green lentils--they almost pop. I did add a smidge of tomato paste and extra vegetable stock to both versions .Haven't tried to add vinegar yet. This will be a new staple for our family--what a way to eat your vegetable!

