Rating: 4
And to the cook who asked if there's a difference in what kind of lentils you use... the answer is yes. The French green lentils are smaller, firmer, and don't soak up as much of the broth as your garden variety "grocery store" lentils. Which are likely to be brown lentils. I find them to be a bit mushier and milder in flavor and soak up alll of the broth necessitating the blending for texture.

Rating: 4
This is probably one of the most flexible recipes for lentil soup as I've found. You can make it as is and it is wonderful and hardy or you can play with it. The best variation I've found so far is to make mushroom stock (dried "fancy" mushrooms, leek, onion, carrot, celery, herbs de provence) for the broth, use fire-roasted tomatoes for a smoky flavor, and then add diced black forest ham in large chunks while the soup simmers for about 30 minutes. Exquisite.

