I chose this recipe because I was searching for a "French" lentil soup, not any lentil soup. So I'm surprised by some of the additions suggested by other reviewers. French lentil soup is classic peasant food, simply prepared with quality ingredients. This recipe comes very close to what I was looking for. For those that suggest adding bay leaf, I'm not sure what that does (the debate on bay is quite extensive, and be sure you are using the true culinary species, not California bay). A French lentil soup would characteristically use thyme for seasoning, so I did add that, and since I'm not vegetarian, I used chicken stock rather than vegetable (not sure how the French would feel about that, but it does add considerably to the flavor). Finally, instead of balsamic vinegar, I used the traditional apple cider vinegar--just two teaspoons for a hint of vinegar. In the end, the soup I made was just a little thicker than what I had in mind.

