I first made this recipe about half a year ago and I've been making it about once a month since. It's part of my resolution to eat less meat by dedicating one day a week to being a vegetarian. I usually end up using much more than 4 cups of homemade vegetable broth (usually about 6-7 cups). I like my soup to have more liquid. I also use half green (puy) lentils and half red lentils, I substitute two fresh tomatoes for the canned tomatoes, and I add a bay leaf to the soup while its simmering. I always blend 2 cups of the solids because it makes the texture of the soup really great. I also add just a bit of balsamic vinegar to the soup as soon as it's off the stove. It's not the prettiest soup, but it's so comforting, filling, and not difficult to make at all.

