Rating: 4
This is a delicious soup. I'd definitely serve it to guests. I followed the modifications by BobrRob from Palatine, IL "I made a double batch with some modifications. 4 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil - 4 cups chopped onions - 2 cups chopped celery stalks - 2 cups chopped carrots - 4 garlic cloves, chopped - 8 cups (4 cans) Swanson Chicken Broth 99% Fat Free - 2 cups lentils, rinsed, drained. Thats 2 cups BEFORE you rinse them - 2 14 1/2ounce can Stewed Tomatoes with Oregano and Basil Pureed - ½ tsp Thyme Leaves - ½ tsp Parsley Flakes - ½ tsp Oregano Leaves - ½ tsp Marjoram Leaves - ½ tsp Tarragon - ½ tsp Sage - ½ tsp Crushed Rosemary - ½ tsp Ground Sea Salt - ½ tsp Ground Pepper - 1 ½ Tbsp Balsamic Vinegar. - Preparation. Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and all the seasonings, except the pepper. Saute garlic until it starts to break down, then add onions, celery, carrots; sauté until vegetables begin to brown, about 25 minutes. Add broth, lentils, and pureed tomatoes with juice and bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until lentils are tender, about 35 minutes. Add pepper. Use a blending stick, on high, 5 passes top to bottom. Came out great."

