Rating: 4
I have several lentil soup recipes but when I made this yesterday , it became my instant favorite. I was fortunate enough to still have a supply of French green lentils and I do agree they have a much richer flavor than regular. The only change I made was not to bother removing 2 cups to a blender, I just used my stick blender right in the pot to puree part of the mixture. This one is a definite keeper and I do love soup.

Rating: 3
This turned out very well - despite the fact that my can of diced tomatoes contained only juice and no diced tomatoes!! I boiled a potato and put it in the soup to thicken it due to lack of tomato. I also pureed it all in a Cuisinart as I dont like soup with lumps of stuff in. I used brown lentils and it turned out great but I will try with French Green Lentils another time. I froze it in batches in my freezer. I added a swirl of cream at the end as I always do with soups. Very nice.